The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	The Indian Football Association (IFA) secretary Utpal Ganguli will announce the date of the meeting to decide Snehasish Chakrabortys fate on Tuesday. The midfielder has alleged that East Bengal forged his signature on the contract in their bid to prevent him from playing for Mohun Bagan in the forthcoming season.       
	Meanwhile, East Bengal released Ashim Biswas who is set to join Chirag United. Chirags Brazilian recruits Joshimar and Eduardo will arrive on Tuesday.          
	 Mohammedan Sportings executive committee decided that the budget for the next season will be Rs 2 crore.       
	It was also decided that there would be week-long celebrations to commemorate the 75th anniversary of their first Calcutta league triumph.          
	 Andrews School were on top of the leaderboard after the first day of the 5th RCGC inter-school golf championship. La Martiniere for Boys (LMB) 1 are second, followed by St Xaviers and LMB 2. In the under-13 category, Don Bosco were tied at the top with LMB juniors 1.           
	 Harshvardhan Goenka won the sub-junior title defeating Dishant Mehta 2-0 in the final of the State Junior Snooker Championship at the Bengal Rowing Club on Saturday.                
	GOLF: Inter-school championship at the RCGC from 7.20am onwards      
	Snooker: State sub-junior meet at the BRC from 11.15am onwards.                                                                                                                                                                       
